name: Unfabulous
overview: Unfabulous is an American children's television series that aired on Nickelodeon. The series is about an "unfabulous" 7th Grade middle school student named Addie Singer, played by Emma Roberts. The show, which debuted in late summer 2004, was one of the most-watched programs in the United States among children between the age of 10 and 16 and was created by Sue Rose, who previously created the animated series Pepper Ann and Angela Anaconda.

episodes.name: The Party
episodes.overview: While trying to survive the first day of 7th grade with her friends, Addie tries to get noticed, other than being noticed from her hot brother. Turns out, Addie gets to throw a party when the previous party host gets a sprained ankle. It's up to Addie to make things go her way. Or, not go her way; dunking her head in a punch bowl.

episodes.name: The Secret
episodes.overview: Addie goes overboard when finally hearing the truth out of Zach and Geena. After they lied so many times to Addie, Addie gives some new rules that Zach and Geena aren't too comfortable with. Meanwhile, Ben has his own problem, while trying to hide from working for his father, or working at the 'Juice' shop.

episodes.name: The Picture
episodes.overview: Picture day is coming up and Addie is ready for it. It is mentioned that if you don't get your picture taken, then you will have to prepare a haiku for the yearbook. Addie is then told by one of the popular kids that her hair is 'flat.' Addie notices this and tries to fix it, only to make it worse. She then must make the decision of being brave and taking the picture or sending in a haiku for the yearbook.

episodes.name: The Book Club
episodes.overview: Addie makes up excuses to get out of her mother's book club. Meanwhile, Ben awaits his father's appearence so he can start his driving lessons.

episodes.name: The Pal
episodes.overview: Addie gets upset when Geena tells her that her and Jake are just pals and nothing more. So she gets all dolled up and starts reading glossy magazine to impress Jake but it makes it worse.  so she decides she doesn't need glossy magazine-or 6 inch high heels to impress Jake.

episodes.name: Pink Guitar
episodes.overview: Addie feels she is ignored and wants to become famous. In an effort to do so, she tries out for an all-girl band called CUTE. She makes it as a guitarist, but discovers the only real thing the band does is dance and pretend to sing and play and quickly quits.

episodes.name: The Rep
episodes.overview: Addie and her classmates are assigned to hang out with a certain team for a school project. Addie is assigned to group 'popular' along with Maris. Turns out, that Addie becoming popular could ruin a friendship with Geena.

episodes.name: The 66th Day
episodes.overview: It's the 66th day that Addie has liked Jake; but it turns into chaos when her CD of 65 songs about Jake ends up in school. Now she's on a frantic search throughout Rocky Road Middle School for the sacred disc, determined to find it before it falls into the wrong hands - she wouldn't even want to think about what would happen.

episodes.name: The List of Kissed
episodes.overview: Addie wants to get her name added to the list on the girls' bathroom wall of those who have been kissed by a boy, so she schemes to make her friend Eli do the deed when they are at the movies.

episodes.name: The B Word
episodes.overview: Addie can't stand Geena's new boyfriend but can't say exactly why.

episodes.name: The Little Sister
episodes.overview: In an attempt to escape from her older brother's shadow, Addie sets out to accomplish something he never did, to get an article published in the school newspaper, but she succeeds in a different way than she expected.

episodes.name: The Partner
episodes.overview: Addie tries to convince Zach to be her partner for the science fair.

episodes.name: The Bar Mitzvah
episodes.overview: Addie gets braces, which means taunting by Cranberry and Maris. But when she's invited to Randy Klein's Bar Mitzvah, she feels insecure about it. With loads of convincing, she goes to the Bar Mitzvah.

episodes.name: The Rhinoceros in the Middle of the Room
The Grey Area
episodes.overview: Addie has to choose between Geena and Maris when the two design new cheerleader uniforms but Addie doesn't want to be accused of choosing Geena just because she's her best friend.

episodes.name: The Perfect Couple
episodes.overview: Addie has always thought of her relationship with Randy as perfect, but when he stands her up on a date, she breaks up with him in anger. Randy apologizes, but  Geena thinks that Addie did the right thing by "kicking him to the curb".  Will Addie forgive Randy, or is the "perfect couple" really split for good?

episodes.name: The Drama
episodes.overview: Addie is chosen to direct the school play and Geena gets the lead in the play. Addie gets jealous because Geena gets to share the lead with Jake Bahari, and she starts trying to sabotage Geena but she ends up sabotaging the play.

episodes.name: The Set Up
episodes.overview: Despite having the best intentions, Geena and Zach fail miserably at helping Addie get over her breakup with Randy.

episodes.name: The Last Day of 7th Grade
episodes.overview: Grad Week, the last days of seventh grade, finds Addie avoiding marauding eight graders and her own feelings for Jake.
